# Git Workflow And Commit Guidelines

Use Git Flow and Conventional Commits unless the team decides otherwise for a specific repository phase.

### Branches

- `main`: production-ready code.
- `develop`: integration branch for the next release.
- `feature/*`: feature work branched from `develop`.
- `release/*`: release preparation branched from `develop`.
- `hotfix/*`: urgent fixes branched from `main`.

Examples:

```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git checkout -b feature/WORK-132-add-login-endpoint
```

```bash
git checkout main
git checkout -b hotfix/WORK-142-fix-token-expiration
```

### Commits

Use Conventional Commits:

```text
type(ticket-number): subject
```

Types:

- `feat`: new feature.
- `fix`: bug fix.
- `docs`: documentation only.
- `style`: formatting only.
- `refactor`: code change that is not a feature or bug fix.
- `test`: tests added or corrected.
- `chore`: build, tooling, or maintenance.

Examples:

```text
feat(WORK-132): Add login endpoint
fix(WORK-142): Resolve token expiration bug
docs(WORK-90): Update setup instructions
refactor(WORK-120): Move user status logic into domain model
test(WORK-131): Add auth endpoint contract tests
chore(WORK-100): Update dependencies
```

Rules:

- Use present tense.
- Keep the subject concise, ideally under 72 characters.
- Include a ticket number when one exists.
- Do not end the subject with a period.
- Keep commits focused and meaningful.

### Pull Requests

Rules:

- PRs target `develop` for normal feature/fix work.
- PRs require at least one approval.
- Use squash merges into `develop` and `release` when the team wants a clean feature history.
- Use merge commits into `main` and from `release` back to `develop` when preserving release history matters.
- Keep PRs focused and small enough to review.
- Update docs when setup, behavior, contracts, or architecture change.
- All relevant tests must pass before merge.

PR checklist:

```markdown
## Description

Brief description of changes.

## Ticket

- [WORK-132](link-to-ticket)

## Type of Change

- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation update

## Testing

- [ ] Unit tests added/updated
- [ ] Integration tests added/updated
- [ ] Contract/API tests added/updated
- [ ] Manual testing completed when needed
```
